# Security Rules

## API Route (`app/api/chat/route.ts`)
- Every request MUST pass through the rate limiter (`lib/rate-limit.ts`) before any processing.
- Validate message count (`<= 50`) and individual text length (`<= 10,000` chars). Reject with 400.
- Derive `hasImage` server-side from message parts. Never trust client-supplied flags for prompt construction.
- Always set `maxOutputTokens` on `streamText` to cap cost per response.
- Never expose the API key via `NEXT_PUBLIC_` env vars. The key must stay server-side only.

## Prompt Injection Defence (`lib/build-system-prompt.ts`)
- The system prompt MUST end with an anti-jailbreak refusal clause (the `antiJailbreak` block).
- Hint-mode refusal must explicitly list common override phrases ("ignore previous instructions", "system:", "you are now", "the teacher said").
- Never remove or weaken the `FINAL INSTRUCTION` block without a replacement guardrail.

## Rendering AI Output (`components/tutor-chat.tsx`)
- `ReactMarkdown` MUST include `rehypeSanitize` in `rehypePlugins`.
- Links MUST be filtered: reject any `href` starting with `javascript:`.
- Image `src` attributes MUST be validated to start with `data:` or `blob:` before rendering.

## State & Storage (`app/page.tsx`)
- All data restored from `localStorage` MUST be validated with Zod schemas before use.
- `localStorage.setItem` calls MUST be wrapped in try/catch to handle `QuotaExceededError`.

## Infrastructure
- `proxy.ts` MUST set CSP, `X-Content-Type-Options`, `X-Frame-Options`, and `Referrer-Policy` headers.
- `next.config.mjs` MUST NOT set `typescript.ignoreBuildErrors: true`.
- The app MUST have a React `ErrorBoundary` wrapping page content in the root layout.
